commits.commitMessage:
Add Sleep Mode analysis script for Hong Kong Sanity Station

This analysis script is used to determine whether sleep mode can be successfully entered according to the below criteria:

Sleep Mode criteria:

1) During Sleep phase, the current should below average sleep current (such as 100 Amp) for 6 seconds consecutively.  If not, error message: "Could not maintain lowest and steady current for 6 seconds xx.xx Amp" should be displayed.

2) The current different after Sleep phase should be more than 15 Amp.  If not error message: "Current diff between Active and Sleep is too less xx.xx Amp" should be display.

Resolves: QTI9X07-4860
Change-Id: I954c738015f37f8a1005daedc92339d50608535b
Signed-off-by: Ray Fan <rfa@sierrawireless.com>
commits.subject: Add Sleep Mode analysis script for Hong Kong Sanity Station

comments.message: suggest using a variable at the top of the file, so it is easier to change to some other value if requirements change.
Added constant variable THRESHOLD_COUNT = 6 at the top (line 15)
Seems an odd filename. Why is r18288 in the name?
Under "sleep_check.py" script, line 26, the Amp log filename is hard coded : "amperageLog_WP7601_r18288.txt".  Therefore, use the same filename to recall the file.
According to "amperageLog_WP7601_r18288.txt" file, Enter Sleep Mode data from line 34 to 93, and Exiting Sleep Mode data from line 95 to 124 (end of line).
Not a huge fan of site-specific logic. Is there a reason this is something that is only done in HKG?
This new "Sleep Mode" analysis is requested by Kenneth Yeung.  Therefore, it may be used for HKG products only.  If this analysis can be propagated to other products, this logic can be removed.

commits.commitMessage:
QTI9X07-144 – Expand QMI test capabilities

Issue Description:

Expands the capabilities of qmitest over ADB and ECM interfaces on
both Windows and Linux platforms.

Root Cause:

- Found that a command which deduces the name of the qmi_message from
  the log file isn't working when there are more than 9 messages.

- Script gets stuck when the number of QMI messages in
  the cfg file is increased.

- Found synchronisation problem between AT and ADB threads.

Solution:

- Used regular expressions concept of '+' for reading
  more than 9 messages.

- Delays have been added at required position to solve the problem of
  script getting stuck and thread synchronisation.

Resolves: QTI9X07-144

Signed-off-by: srikanth.s01 <srikanth.s01@infosys.com>
commits.subject: QTI9X07-144 – Expand QMI test capabilities
